metadata.name: Amplitude #210
metadata.description:
Amplitude is a study in depth. Waves travel across the frame using Perlin noise to guide its modulation. Allowing slight variations to occur in each layer. Sometimes the waves are added to the frame and sometimes they are subtracted. Resulting in dramatically different visual appearances. 

Like most of my work this piece is carefully designed to also exist IRL as a 12 layer laser carved woodcut. 
https://alleditions.art/p/amplitude

Arrow keys - adjust the perspective

DESIGNED FOR IRL
Shift P - for a PNG
Shift E - to explode the layers
Shift S - for an SVG

metadata.name: Plottable Era: (I) Primitive #173
metadata.description:
'Plottable Era: (I) Primitive' is the first generator in the "Era" generators series, highlighting different periods and civilizations. This first series "Primitive" shows the beginning of mankind with people exploring the mountains and traveling on the sea during sunset.

The digital version simulates ink effects and adds a subtle animation over the water. Each outcome is also physically plottable with pens: A SVG file can be exported (right-click save) to plot the piece physically. The plots are designed to be executed in A4 format on either fountain pens (on white paper) or gel pens (Black / Blue).

Thanks to the utility token decoupling, you can get a physical version: the digital NFT is the recipe to a plottable art piece, owning it confers the right to plot or request a physical plot from @greweb (https://greweb.me/plots/nft). @greweb would use fountain pens but other plotting artists are free to achieve it with their own materials and ship to collectors – as long as NFT is owned at request time.

More details and Source code: https://github.com/gre/gre/tree/master/doodles/plottable-era-primitive

@greweb – 2022 – tech: WebGL + Rust + WASM – CC BY-SA 4.0 https://creativecommons.org/licenses/by-sa/4.0/

reserve is set to previous 2022 physical plot collectors.

metadata.name: Cosmic Type #247
metadata.description:
Cosmic Type is a kinetic type experiment that explores both graphic space as structural and semantic agency. Inspired by the early pioneering work of the concrete poets such as Dom Sylvester Houédard, Ian Hamilton Finley and Steve McCaffe, the project is a play with letters, words and graphic form in the computational and generative space.

Each iteration gives you the possibility to discover a variety of visual form through exploring the system. Please explore your iteration with the key interactions below. It is hoped that you give the time to explore and observe. If you don't, you may end up with just a blank canvas. 

Thank you for collecting. 

Key Interactions

‘a’ activates forward motion on/off
‘b’ activates backward motion on/off
‘r’ rotates grid 45° [ rotates on key pressed]
‘f’ rotates the grid freely [ stops on key release ]
‘p’ switches grid scale on/off [ this can be CPU heavy on older machines ] 
‘g’ extra glyphs on/off
‘q’ return to the initial state 


Program written by Mark Webster
Font is copyright ©simonrenaud

metadata.name: Contort #322
metadata.description:
Contort is the result of combining several previously meaningless experiments and learnings into a single cohesive algorithm. The project comes in a variety of shapes, bends, twists, colors, and other variations.  

The artwork builds towards the end-result by rendering a fixed number of forms per frame to ensure a smooth rendering process. Rendering times can vary depending on which features are combined by the hash.

metadata.name: 𝐃𝐞𝐚𝐫𝐭𝐡 #108
metadata.description:
Witness hundreds of small geometric objects gather under one roof to create a cosmic rain!

Ever since I was a child, I have always been good with geometric objects. I used to draw objects such as cubes, cylinders and prisms on paper for hours. As if I'm getting lost in every line between those geometric objects! In this way, every detail of geometry in my daily life and in my other existing life attracts my attention.

Recently, I have been doing research on colors and color palettes, it is really impressive how thousands of color mixtures affect each other and the psychology of living things!

∽∽depending on the screen size you can get different resolutions, which brings out a different side of the project! so you can run this project on all screen sizes and get the output!∽∽

Key:
- Press "s" to export an PNG image


Made with p5.js

metadata.name: CHX-1 #181
metadata.description:
Glitching pixels like it’s 1999.

Inspired by 90’s digital aesthetics, CHX-1 takes a random selection of GAN seeds, combines them in unique ways, and processes them –individually and as a group– with a series of glitching dithering algorithms. Generating fun, original, colorful artworks. Millions of possibilities. Have fun!

<<< Base seeds generated offline using personal styleGAN2-ADA models. Image processing and combinations done generatively by the CHX-1 algorithm >>>

GAN –> p5js –> Blockchain


• Artworks can take a few seconds to load when running live code.

• Press “s” (when "open live" is active) to save a PNG image.
